TITLE: Tim White, longtime WWE referee, dead at 68
SUMMARY: WWE announced Sunday that longtime referee Tim White died at 68. He was the referee during the legendary Undertaker-Mankind Hell in a Cell match.

TITLE: Austin City Council approves resolution to 'explore every option' of raising age to buy AR-15 style weapons
SUMMARY: The Austin City Council voted to approve a resolution that would allow the city explore plans to increase the minimum age to buy an AR-15 style weapon.

TITLE: Jennifer Lopez introduces her child Emme, 14, using gender-neutral pronouns during LA performance
SUMMARY: Jennifer Lopez introduced her child, Emme, 14, using gender-neutral pronouns during their first performance together since Super Bowl 'Halftime' in 2020.

TITLE: FINA approves 'gender inclusion policy' for transgender swimmers
SUMMARY: FINA approved a new policy for transgender athletes, which will go into effect on Monday

TITLE: Pompeo says Biden's Iran talks ‘squandered’ Middle East stability: ‘Putting us all at risk’
SUMMARY: In a Sunday interview, former Secretary of State Mike Pompeo told Fox News that President Biden's approach to the Middle East has been a big step in the wrong direction.

TITLE: Texas drive-by shooting at family BBQ leaves 2 dead, 5 wounded: police
SUMMARY: Two men were killed and five other victims were wounded after a suspect drove by a family barbeque in San Antonio and unloaded multiple rounds, authorities said.

TITLE: Hundreds gather for vigil remembering two California police officers killed in shootout
SUMMARY: A vigil was held in El Monte, California, honoring fallen officers Michael Paredes and Joseph Santana, who died following a shootout in the Los Angeles County city.

TITLE: Biden DOJ 'legitimizing' attacks on pro-life centers by not prosecuting Kavanaugh home protesters: Sen. Lee
SUMMARY: Sen. Mike Lee said he was not satisfied with the FBI's response to attacks on pro-life centers, as the Biden DOJ has refused to prosecute protesters at Brett Kavanaugh's home.

TITLE: Hillary Clinton suggests transgender debate 'should not be a priority' for Dems
SUMMARY: Hillary Clinton says the Democratic Party should not treat the transgender debate as a priority, saying the Party should focus on winning elections instead.

TITLE: Reds' Graham Ashcraft told to remove wedding ring during substance check
SUMMARY: Graham Ashcraft was forced to remove his wedding band during the Cincinnati Reds' loss to the Milwaukee Brewers.

TITLE: Juneteenth: What is it and why do we celebrate it?
SUMMARY: Juneteenth is a federal holiday that commemorates the day enslaved people in Texas learned the Emancipation Proclamation freed slaves in Confederate states.

TITLE: Box Office: Pixar's 'Lightyear' Underwhelms With $51 Million Debut as 'Jurassic World' Stays No. 1
SUMMARY: Pixar's "Lightyear" fell short at the box office, bringing in $51 million in North American ticket sales, becoming one of the only Disney films to not take the top spot.

TITLE: Number of Americans who believe in God drops to historic low: Poll
SUMMARY: The number of Americans who believe in God is at the lowest in nearly seven decades, as Gallup notes religiosity is a major factor in US political divisions.

TITLE: US Open 2022: Grayson Murray tosses putter, bends iron over knee during frustrating final round
SUMMARY: Grayson Murray had a frustrating outing in the final round of the US Open on Sunday and took it out on his golf clubs.

TITLE: Biden admin explores bussing migrants to US towns hours beyond border
SUMMARY: President Joe Biden and DHS Sec. Alejandro Mayorkas are drafting plans to send busloads of migrants to U.S. towns hours beyond the border, Republican lawmakers say.

TITLE: Third suspect charged in Chicago mass shooting at McDonald’s near Magnificent Mile
SUMMARY: Chicago police say a 17-year-old turned himself in on a gun offense, making him the third suspect arrested following a mass shooting at a McDonald’s near Magnificent Mile last month.

TITLE: Summer travel might not take off as expected due to 'challenging' labor shortages, pilot warns
SUMMARY: President of the Southwest Airlines Pilots Association Captain Casey Murray explains what consumers dealing with flight cancelations and delays can expect for the rest of the summer.

TITLE: Wisconsin mom says school district threatening legal action to 'bully' her criticism to silence
SUMMARY: A Wisconsin mom said that the Oconomowoc School District is trying to bully her into silence by threatening legal action for her critical statements.

TITLE: Republicans mulling run for president not waiting on Trump
SUMMARY: Prominent Republicans looking to launch their own political campaigns are not waiting for Donald Trump to announce his own candidacy ahead of the 2024 election.

TITLE: Longtime WWE referee Dave Hebner dead at 73
SUMMARY: WWE announced longtime pro-wrestling referee Dave Hebner died. He was 73.
